PURPOSE OF JOB:
The Data Analyst is responsible for interpreting data and turning it into information that can offer ways to improve processes, thus affecting business decisions. This role also gathers information from various sources and interprets patterns and trends, and often makes recommendations about the methods and ways in which Class Valuation obtains and analyzes data to improve the quality and the efficiency of data systems.

Spokeo is a people search engine that both enlightens and empowers our customers. With over 12 billion records and 18 million visitors per month, we reconnect friends, reunite families, prevent fraud, and more.
As a Data Optimization Analyst at Spokeo, you will have the opportunity to combine programming, algorithms and quantitative analysis to optimize our data quality and key metrics for high volume data pipelines, integrating multiple sources. You will be responsible for leveraging data mining approaches to systematically recognize patterns and data anomalies intended to inform data cleaning, search-ability, and identity resolution. This is a hands-on development/analytics position focused on automating processes that ensure the integrity of the data that we provide to our customers. You should be open to working with diverse types of big data and technologies such as Amazon AWS, MapReduce/Spark, Tableau, and Pentaho. The ideal candidate should possess expertise in data mining large and complex datasets using Python and Spark.

This is a remote position.

Job Description

This Data Analyst position is to work with Business Teams and bridge the gap between Judiciary business partners and the technology solution providers by translating business needs into Warehouse solutions for BI.
Data Analyst should have extensive SQL writing experience. This position will also involve identification/Verifications of test plans to ensure that technical solutions meet the needs of the business.
In addition to being experienced in gathering and documenting requirements, facilitating meetings, and delivering results, this person must also be a highly organized, self-starter who thrives in a fast-paced and rapidly changing environment.
The ideal candidate will be responsible for working closely with Research Analysts to assist with conducting data analysis to make informed decisions. The ideal will also conduct data extraction via SQL as well as prepare and document data requirements and conduct data validation for the automation of data extractions to be used in analytics. The candidate will have experience in designing new data warehouse structures to meet business needs. The candidate must:
-Using excellent communication skills, work closely with lines of business, including Research Analysts to address data needs for analytics.
-Be proficient in SQL.
-Analyze raw system data.
-Mine large datasets and draw valid inferences and actionable insights.
-Use SQL to extract data from a large and complex data warehouse and conduct analysis to ensure the proper data is available to support business needs.
-Align data attributes across disparate systems to ensure common connection points are utilized when joining or integrating data sets.
-Work with technical teams to identify data sources.
-Prepare data requirements, data models and transformation rules for new data warehouse structures, including summary information optimized for analytics.
-Identify areas to increase efficiency and automation of data-related processes.
-Create test cases and perform quality validation of data warehouse content to ensure accuracy.
-Create data flow diagrams to illustrate data lineage and mapping from the data warehouse to end-point publication.
-Analyze code in BI tools (e.g., WebFocus, Tableau) to determine data usage and assist with determining the data usage accuracy.
-Conduct data profiling to identify data quality issues and work with Business and IT teams to resolve the issues.

Responsibilities
Gather client requirements for data migration, understand their current system architecture, implement best practices
Extract data from the client's old system (various databases, flat files, and web apps)
Strong understanding of data to analyze and profile source system
Present the source data points to the client for effective data migration
Prepare a data map that will be presented to the client for their approval
Transform data primarily using TSQL (and other tools as needed)
Able to effectively take data mapping sign-off from clients
